This project uses a comprehensive design token system located in `src/styles/tokens/`. All tokens are defined as SCSS variables and CSS custom properties for maximum flexibility and theme support.

## Token Organization

The design tokens are organized into the following categories:

- **Colors** (`colors.scss`) - Brand colors, neutrals, semantic colors, and theme mappings
- **Typography** (`typography.scss`) - Font families, sizes, weights, and text styles
- **Spacing** (`spacing.scss`) - 4px grid-based spacing scale
- **Sizing** (`sizing.scss`) - Component sizes, heights, widths
- **Radius** (`radius.scss`) - Border radius values
- **Elevation** (`elevation.scss`) - Shadow and depth tokens
- **Motion** (`motion.scss`) - Animation durations and easing curves
- **Layout** (`layout.scss`) - Breakpoints, grid system, and container widths

All tokens are imported through `src/styles/tokens/index.scss` using `@forward`.

## Design System

This project uses **Carbon Design System** (from `@carbon/react`) as the UI component library. The custom design tokens complement and extend Carbon's existing token system while maintaining compatibility.

**Related Documentation:** See `.builder/rules/theming-system.mdc` for complete theming system documentation including how themes work, theme switching, and theme persistence.

## Color Tokens

### Brand Identity
The primary brand color is **green**, reflecting the InsureCo insurance brand:
- Brand green scale: `$color-brand-green-10` through `$color-brand-green-100`
- Primary brand color: `$color-brand-green-60` (#198038)

### Secondary Brand Colors
Additional brand color palettes:
- Red scale: `$color-brand-red-10` through `$color-brand-red-100`
- Blue scale: `$color-brand-blue-10` through `$color-brand-blue-100`

### Neutral Palette
Grey scale from light to dark:
- `$color-grey-10` (#f4f4f4) to `$color-grey-100` (#161616)

### Semantic Colors
- **Success**: Green (`$color-success-60`)
- **Warning**: Yellow/Orange (`$color-warning-60`)
- **Error**: Red (`$color-error-60`)
- **Info**: Blue (`$color-info-60`)

### Theme Support
The color system supports both light and dark themes using CSS custom properties:

**Light Theme** (default, white, g10):
- Background: white to light grey
- Text: dark grey to black
- Interactive: brand green 60
- Form fields: white background, dark text

**Dark Theme** (g90, g100):
- Background: dark grey to near-black
- Text: light grey to white
- Interactive: brand green 50
- Form fields: dark grey background (#262626), light text

### Form Field Colors
Dedicated tokens ensure form inputs remain readable in both themes:
- `--field-background`: Input field background color
- `--field-text`: Input field text color
- `--field-placeholder`: Placeholder text color

These tokens handle all input states including autofill, preventing white backgrounds in dark mode. See `.builder/rules/form-field-theming.mdc` for complete documentation.

### Usage

// SCSS variables (compile-time)
.my-component {
  background-color: $color-brand-red-60;
  color: $light-text-primary;
}

// CSS custom properties (runtime, theme-aware)
.my-component {
  background-color: var(--interactive-primary);
  color: var(--text-primary);
}


**Best Practice**: Use theme-aware CSS custom properties (e.g., `--text-primary`, `--background-primary`) instead of static colors to ensure proper dark/light theme support.

